legacy.full_text: 🎙️Pat Nevin: “The club I am truly fearful for is not a newly promoted side. If I am brutally honest, my real concerns are for my old club Everton.” https://t.co/71sd4hy6RM

I was told by FSG lovers we will be active in August. Went for a player who rejected every club before, and now possibly going for someone at Everton who definitely won’t sell. I mean, come on, how much more of this bullshit are we gonna take as fans?

"I've learnt pretty quickly what it means to people."

The boss on Goodison Park's final season. 🏟️ https://t.co/xmRcMRNC2j

The contrast

‘Everton expects success. We’ve a very good crowd... they pay money and expect to see us do well. If we don’t do well… something will be done about it.’

‘At this football club, if you’re not doing well and you’re not winning, that’s what happens (empty seats)’ https://t.co/kg6cbA90Sw

result.text:
#EVEBHA – 47’ VAR OVERTURN

The referee awarded a penalty to Everton for a foul by Dunk on Calvert-Lewin. The VAR recommended an on-field review as he deemed Calvert-Lewin’s foot landed on Dunk’s foot and there was no foul. The referee overturned the original decision and play restarted with a drop ball.
